<subSubSection id="C37D3D94FFEEF35AD14C93E8D8E3FF07" box="[365,913,218,245]" pageId="26" pageNumber="203" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8BD86E1FFFEEF35AD14C93E8D8E3FF07" blockId="26.[365,913,218,245]" box="[365,913,218,245]" pageId="26" pageNumber="203">
<heading id="D090D973FFEEF35AD14C93E8D8E3FF07" bold="true" box="[365,913,218,245]" centered="true" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="26" pageNumber="203" reason="2">
<emphasis id="B913B20DFFEEF35AD14C93E8D8E3FF07" bold="true" box="[365,913,218,245]" pageId="26" pageNumber="203">
Misidentifications of 
<taxonomicName id="4C67159CFFEEF35AD25B93E9D8E3FF07" baseAuthorityName="Bernhauer" baseAuthorityYear="1934" box="[634,913,218,245]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Thinodromus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="203" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="capensis">
<emphasis id="B913B20DFFEEF35AD25B93E9D8E3FF07" bold="true" box="[634,913,218,245]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="203">Thinodromus capensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37D3D94FFEEF35AD0949227D8FDFE9E" pageId="26" pageNumber="203" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD86E1FFFEEF35AD0949227D8FDFE9E" blockId="26.[151,1127,276,364]" pageId="26" pageNumber="203">
The identity of 
<taxonomicName id="4C67159CFFEEF35AD1439226D927FEDE" baseAuthorityName="Bernhauer" baseAuthorityYear="1934" box="[354,597,277,300]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Thinodromus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="203" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="capensis">
<emphasis id="B913B20DFFEEF35AD1439226D927FEDE" box="[354,597,277,300]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="203">Thinodromus capensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was unclear for a long time, and three different species were identified under this name by previous authors. Below I am treating 
<taxonomicName id="4C67159CFFEEF35AD3D09206DF15FEBE" baseAuthorityName="Bernhauer" baseAuthorityYear="1934" box="[1009,1127,309,332]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Thinodromus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="203" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="capensis">
<emphasis id="B913B20DFFEEF35AD3D09206DF15FEBE" box="[1009,1127,309,332]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="203">T. capensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as well as both species with which it was previously confused in detail.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
